headline: In Gaza, the fate of thousands missing remains unknown
description: In the Palestinian enclave, thousands of families don't know the fate of their loved ones: Some bodies lie beneath the rubble, others were pulverized by the strikes or taken away by the Israeli army.

headline: Between Putin and Trump, a similarity born of hatred, contempt and revisionism
Murdered teacher Samuel Paty's family stands united against 'indecent' defense at appeal trial
'The US always promises to extract itself from Middle Eastern quagmires while continuing to get stuck knee-deep'
description: After one year in the White House, Donald Trump has ordered more missile and drone strikes than his predecessor did over the entirety of his term, writes Le Monde columnist Gilles Paris.

headline: Marine Le Pen's 2027 presidential bid further jeopardized by prosecution at her appeal trial
description: By requesting a five-year ban on election to public office on February 3, the prosecution has fueled doubts about Marine Le Pen's ability to run in the 2027 presidential election. The appeals court is due to rule on the case by the summer.

headline: British mothers fight the slow poison of industrial pollution in Corby
description: In Corby, once a major center for the British steel industry, the dismantling of steelworks massively exposed the population to toxic substances, causing widespread pollution, birth defects and pediatric cancers. A group of mothers has waged a long battle to raise national awareness about this major public health issue.

headline: Human Rights Watch's Philippe Bolopion: 'The US has become hostile to human rights'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, the head of the human rights advocacy group expressed surprise 'at how quickly the quality of American democracy has deteriorated in just one year.'

description: 'I wouldn't be where I am today if...' In this series, Le Monde interviews a personality about a decisive moment in their life. The figure skater and former Olympic champion looks back on a childhood filled with constraints in order to succeed in a demanding and conservative environment.

headline: Iran cracks down on medical workers treating protesters
description: Arrests, threats and intimidation of doctors and nurses have escalated, as authorities demand the identities of those treated during protests.

headline: France's 2026 budget battle is finally over. The next one may be even more complex.
description: The Finance Ministry is already working on the next budget bill. On paper, France will need to make a deficit reduction effort twice as great as in 2026. It will be a daunting challenge, so close to the presidential election.
